    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>"A traditional school can help a student only after he fails, in summer school. That's like allowing a swimmer to drown before rescuing him." -- Charles McCasland, a principal in Plano, Tex.  [ 22:1. ]</p>
